WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000
You can usually think of problems in released software as coming from things that

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:07.000
people forgot to test and what that means is testing was inadequate and

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:09.000
the developers were unaware of that fact.

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:13.000
What we're going to look at this week is a collection of techniques called code coverage

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:16.000
where automated tools can tell us places where our testing strategy

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:18.000
is not doing a good job and that's a very powerful and useful--

